	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=95975><span id= >Hunngus</span></a><br><span id=notbold>5 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I made my first one of these today. I did this with a 168 pottery skill and 213 wisdom (with Insight cast on me) on the 1st try. I failed on the next 4 attempts however. It took some research to find the info online, and it wasn't 100% correct, so I will post what I know here...<br><br>Ingredients to make the Unfired Idol: (combine in pottery wheel)<br>1 Large Block of Magic Clay<br>1 Vial of Clear Mana<br>1 Imbued Gem<br>Sculpting Tools<br><br>To create the Finished Idol: (combine in kiln)<br>1 Divine Glaze<br>1 HQ Firing Sheet<br>1 Unfired Idol<br><br>To make and collect the individual ingredients is the tough part. But you also need to enlist the help of a rogue and enchanter as well. (if you are not one already)<br>An enchanter can use the Enchant Clay spell to make magic clay.<br>Vial of Clear Mana is created using the enchanter spell Clarify Mana, but requires an Emerald and a Poison Vial.<br>Gems are imbued by a cleric or druid of that faith. You must select the proper gem for the kind of Idol you want to make. (gem listing to follow)<br>Sculpting Tools can be bought from several pottery vendors.<br><br>Divine Glaze is created by combining the following components in a Mortar Bowl: (also available at pottery merchants)<br>1 White Lead<br>1 Iron Oxide<br>1 Permafrost Crystals<br>1 Flask of Water<br><br>A rogue with poison making skills can create White Lead by combining Lead Sulfide and Limestone. (these are readily available at the merchant outside the Kaladim Bank)<br>Iron Oxide is a ground spawn in Steamfont around the large cogs by the Minotaur Caves.<br>Permafrost Crystals are ground spawn in Permafrost Keep.<br><br>Here is a listing of Gems and the Deity they belong to:<br>Bertoxxulous-Black Sapphire<br>Brell-Ruby<br>Bristlebane-Periot<br>Cazic-Amber<br>Erollisi-Rose Quartz<br>Inny-Sapphire<br>Karana-Plains Pebble<br>Mithaniel-Diamond<br>Quellious-Topaz<br>Rallos-Jade<br>Rodeet-Opal<br>Solusek-Fire Opal<br>Tribunal-Ivory<br>Tunare-Emerald<br><br>I hope this information saves you valuable time, and wish you luck in this project.<br><br>Tules</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
